Where do you like to eat in your country?

My favourite place to eat in Muscat is Tawi Dhino – opposite the Sultan Qaboos Grand Mosque in Muttrah Corniche. For me, this place offers all of the Omani dishes in one space and it is conveniently located in the heart of the city. In addition, the authentic grilled meat Tanzy is always a treat to my taste buds and I love their homemade Falafel- a deep fried snack usually prepared with herbs, onions and mashed chickpeas. So tasty yet also good for the belly.

What is your favourite beach in your country?

As a snorkelist and diver I mainly go to Al-Suwaiq (20 km from the Azaiba) but I also love Qantab beach (near Boushar) and Quriyat (about 160 km from Muscat) for the white sands, crystal clear water and the “smooth” waves (similar to those in Goa, India, where I used to live).

Back to the iconic song of this country- Say You Love Me, what does it really mean in the context of your country and culture? And in Oman, how do we say ‘Kiss me’ in Arabic?

Kiss
